ll have his/her name engraved on the trophy and pass it along to the next year's winner. This year the trophy went to Cascade's Eric Bone, who finished the 3.4k course in 18:36. Many thanks to the meet staff and everyone who helped with beginner instruction and other tasks.","external_links":[],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Course Designer","individual_id":"019b8163-5204-757f-889d-4e0cd497f294","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Harvey Friedman","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Finishes","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-7139-aa9f-e67cde450b6c","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Bill Cusworth","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Marker Pickup","individual_id":"019b8163-5204-757f-889d-4e0cd497f294","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Harvey Friedman","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Meet Director","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-7ef7-909c-53557520255d","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Don Atkinson","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Park Permit","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-797d-8bf4-ebd4508c4277","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Dave Tallent","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-70bb-8a36-b4b700fb52d4","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Ardis Dull","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration","individual_id":"019b7ad3-42ab-7c80-8aa6-ca0b226707df","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Rick Hood","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Starts","individual_id":"019b7b4b-9f59-7c25-8af6-a52b1eb143b3","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Bruce McAllister","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"Web Snapshot: Bo Powell Memorial - Woodland Park (1999-09-11)","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"The weather was ideal, with sunny skies and temperatures near 70, for the first annual Bo Powell Memorial Orienteering meet, held at Woodland Park on September 11. Bo Powell, one of the founders of the Cascade Orienteering Club, died last year. Len Englund, another of the club's founders, urged the club to establish a meet in his memory, so this year the first annual Bo Powell Memorial Orienteering Meet was held at Woodland Park. Bo's widow, Kathy, generously donated his compass to the club. This compass was used to create the Bo Powell Memorial Trophy, which will be presented to the fastest finisher on the long course each year. The recipient will have his/her name engraved on the trophy and pass it along to the next year's winner. This year the trophy went to Cascade's Eric Bone, who finished the 3.4k course in 18:36. Many thanks to the meet staff and everyone who helped with beginner instruction and other tasks."}
